01:33.224 --> 01:38.330
<i> ♪ Siren Siren ♪</i>

01:40.432 --> 01:46.305
<i> ♪ Like a warning
 Day is dawning in my heart ♪</i>

01:50.843 --> 01:55.147
<i> ♪ In my heart ♪</i>

01:58.284 --> 02:03.156
<i> ♪ And that desert
 from a seashore ♪</i>

02:04.722 --> 02:09.862
<i> ♪ Feeling somehow
 I've been here before ♪</i>

02:10.862 --> 02:17.203
<i> ♪ And though the light
 is growing darker ♪</i>

02:17.235 --> 02:22.875
<i> ♪ Somehow there's sunlight
 on the way ♪</i>

02:22.907 --> 02:24.877
( TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING )

02:26.945 --> 02:29.448
( CAR HORN HONKING )

02:29.480 --> 02:30.750
[DRIVER]
Get off the road!

02:30.782 --> 02:31.883
Sorry!

02:31.918 --> 02:35.254
Mom, next time can you
drop me off on the other side?

02:35.287 --> 02:36.588
Sorry, honey.

02:46.564 --> 02:48.867
( BELL RINGS )

02:52.003 --> 02:56.209
Oh-- hey!

02:56.241 --> 02:57.409
So what you're saying is,
if I punch you...

02:57.443 --> 02:58.711
your bones will break like
toothpicks?

02:58.743 --> 03:00.346
Come on.

02:58.743 --> 03:00.346
Yes, that's what I'm saying.

03:00.378 --> 03:01.614
How about we give it a try?

03:01.646 --> 03:03.316
[SIREN] Hey! Leave him alone!

03:03.348 --> 03:05.584
This isn't your fight, Siren.
Get out of here.

03:05.617 --> 03:06.985
You know I can scream
loud enough.

03:07.019 --> 03:08.987
I'll get Principal Strauss
out here in a heart beat.

03:09.020 --> 03:10.155
So?

03:10.188 --> 03:12.490
Last I heard, you're one scream
away from being expelled.

03:12.524 --> 03:14.759
Whatever, we were just playing
around, right, brittle boy?

03:14.793 --> 03:16.528
Yeah.

03:18.631 --> 03:20.332
Thanks.

03:20.366 --> 03:21.867
What was all that about?

03:20.366 --> 03:21.867
Nothing.

03:21.900 --> 03:24.403
That didn't look like nothing.

03:24.436 --> 03:26.472
She found out about this.

03:27.605 --> 03:30.710
It's a form of Osteogenesis
Imperfecta.

03:30.742 --> 03:32.677
It just means my
bones are very fragile.

03:32.711 --> 03:34.280
Like all the time?

03:34.312 --> 03:37.315
Every day for the rest
of my life.

03:37.348 --> 03:39.518
Thanks for stepping in, though.

03:43.889 --> 03:45.925
( BELL RINGS )

03:50.028 --> 03:51.897
Gross! Stop.

03:52.931 --> 03:55.768
All right, everyone,
settle down.

03:55.800 --> 03:58.470
First things first, we do have a
new student joining our school.

03:58.503 --> 04:01.540
Please give a warm welcome to
Adam Wiltz. Adam, please stand.

04:05.076 --> 04:06.512
Hello.

04:07.645 --> 04:10.582
The floor is yours,
introduce yourself.

04:10.616 --> 04:12.018
I'm Adam.

04:12.050 --> 04:13.085
What's wrong with you?

04:13.118 --> 04:15.487
A better way of asking that
question would be...

04:15.520 --> 04:16.954
what's different about you?

04:16.988 --> 04:20.725
Okay, then what's
different about you?

04:20.759 --> 04:23.795
I have what's called
brittle bone disease.

04:23.829 --> 04:25.798
Oh, that sucks.

04:25.831 --> 04:27.033
Crystal!

04:27.065 --> 04:30.637
No, she's right, it does suck.

04:32.571 --> 04:34.073
Hayden!

04:34.105 --> 04:36.509
We talked about throwing paper!

04:36.541 --> 04:38.943
What's something else
you threw last time?

04:38.976 --> 04:40.945
Was it your sandwich?

04:40.978 --> 04:42.947
Are you all done, Adam?

04:42.980 --> 04:44.149
Uh, yeah.

04:44.182 --> 04:46.985
All right, well now that you've
been properly introduced...

04:47.019 --> 04:48.586
let's get back to studying!

04:48.620 --> 04:50.923
Okay, don't make friends
with the new kid.

04:50.956 --> 04:52.992
It's social suicide.

04:53.024 --> 04:56.361
I don't know, I kind
of like him.

04:58.430 --> 04:59.732
Metamorphosis.

04:59.764 --> 05:02.567
A biological process in which
an animal...

05:02.600 --> 05:03.868
goes through an abrupt change...

05:03.901 --> 05:05.937
due to something called
differentiation.

05:05.971 --> 05:07.906
Now can anyone tell me
another animal...

05:07.939 --> 05:09.809
that goes through
metamorphosis?

05:12.877 --> 05:13.979
Siren...

05:18.516 --> 05:20.752
Siren?

05:21.920 --> 05:23.456
Um...

05:23.488 --> 05:24.589
Mermaids?

05:26.425 --> 05:29.362
Mermaids aren't real, Crystal.

05:29.394 --> 05:30.430
What don't you try
something else...

05:30.463 --> 05:32.498
like a different type
of fish or a caterpillar?

05:32.531 --> 05:35.768
Did you know that
metamorphosis is a Greek word?

05:35.800 --> 05:38.603
Meta is a prefix that means
after--

05:38.637 --> 05:41.708
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

05:43.742 --> 05:45.745
( GASPS )

05:47.112 --> 05:48.080
What is it, Siren?

05:48.112 --> 05:50.016
I have to go to the bathroom!

05:51.048 --> 05:53.985
( CHUCKLING )

05:54.019 --> 05:57.389
All right, everyone, settle
down. Eyes back up front.

05:57.423 --> 05:58.891
[MRS. HARPER]
You can't control nature.

06:01.026 --> 06:03.629
Where do you think you're going,
young lady?

06:03.661 --> 06:06.098
Siren, you get back here!

06:10.935 --> 06:13.972
Oh, hey there, Siren,
everything okay?

06:17.475 --> 06:18.778
Yes!

06:18.810 --> 06:21.880
<i> ( SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

06:32.658 --> 06:35.561
( DOOR OPENS, CLOSES )

06:35.593 --> 06:36.928
What are you doing home?

06:36.961 --> 06:38.930
Nothing, Mom!
School is canceled!

06:38.963 --> 06:41.033
What do you mean, it's canceled?

06:52.711 --> 06:54.213
[TIFFANY]
Siren, are you okay?

06:54.245 --> 06:57.983
Fine, Mom, just let me be
for a minute.

06:59.951 --> 07:02.889
<i> ( SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES )</i>

07:09.661 --> 07:11.096
( KNOCKING ON DOOR )

07:11.129 --> 07:12.798
I said I needed a minute, Mom!

07:12.831 --> 07:16.535
I'm not your mom.
Okay, what's going on?

07:16.567 --> 07:18.770
I've never seen you break
a single rule before.

07:18.803 --> 07:20.673
Now you're ditching school?

07:20.706 --> 07:21.973
You ran out of class after me?

07:22.007 --> 07:24.810
No, I went to the bathroom.
Duh.

07:24.843 --> 07:27.146
[SIREN]
Cute, you can go home.

07:27.178 --> 07:31.750
Please, your face has psycho
written all over it.

07:34.052 --> 07:35.621
So what happened?

07:35.653 --> 07:38.557
Did you get your period?

07:35.653 --> 07:38.557
What? No!

07:38.589 --> 07:40.892
Okay, so is it a boy?

07:38.589 --> 07:40.892
No.

07:40.925 --> 07:43.094
Is it that new kid?

07:40.925 --> 07:43.094
No!

07:43.127 --> 07:44.963
A girl?

07:44.997 --> 07:47.867
Okay, well, I didn't come all
this way to play guessing games.

07:47.899 --> 07:49.501
Spill it.

07:49.535 --> 07:51.737
Okay, sit down.

07:49.535 --> 07:51.737
Okay.

07:59.610 --> 08:02.647
<i> ( WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

08:04.149 --> 08:05.216
What are we doing?

08:05.250 --> 08:07.487
Just wait.

08:14.326 --> 08:15.661
( KNOCK ON DOOR )

08:15.694 --> 08:17.763
Knock, knock. Mini sandwiches!

08:17.795 --> 08:20.598
Yay! You're the best,
Mrs. Phillips.

08:20.632 --> 08:22.935
Try to convince Siren of that.

08:22.968 --> 08:24.036
I will...

08:24.069 --> 08:26.605
if she stops acting
like a crazy person.

08:26.637 --> 08:28.706
All right, well, you know,
have fun.

08:28.740 --> 08:31.210
It's not every day that school
gets canceled.

08:33.578 --> 08:35.580
What is this? Have a little
respect for your room?

08:35.614 --> 08:37.615
Mom, out!

08:37.649 --> 08:41.921
What? I'm just saying, the
solution is less pollution.

08:44.855 --> 08:46.292
Fish sandwiches.

08:49.827 --> 08:50.962
Is something wrong?

08:50.995 --> 08:52.564
It tastes funny.

08:53.631 --> 08:55.800
Since we're not in school,
you want to go to the beach?

08:55.833 --> 08:57.102
Mm, okay.

09:00.672 --> 09:02.707
Whoa! Take it easy
on that thing.

09:02.740 --> 09:05.110
What? I'm thirsty.

09:05.143 --> 09:08.147
So, has your mom talked to you
about anything lately?

09:08.179 --> 09:11.250
My mom talks to me
about all kinds of things...

09:11.283 --> 09:12.750
all the time.

09:12.783 --> 09:15.620
Well, anything unusual?

09:15.653 --> 09:19.057
She gave me a lecture on
properly watering the lawn.

09:19.091 --> 09:20.826
Is that what you mean?

09:20.859 --> 09:23.663
What about your
birthday next week?

09:26.163 --> 09:28.299
Or your body?

09:28.332 --> 09:29.634
My body?

09:29.668 --> 09:31.937
What are you talking about?

09:31.970 --> 09:34.206
Never mind.

09:38.309 --> 09:40.745
You feel like people
are watching us?

09:42.880 --> 09:44.916
Well, we are pretty cute.

09:44.950 --> 09:47.786
Not like 'those two are
adorable' kind of stares.

09:47.818 --> 09:49.154
More like...

09:51.222 --> 09:54.993
psychotic killer kind of stares.

09:56.360 --> 09:58.730
Come on, let's go
somewhere more quiet.

10:03.835 --> 10:06.906
(<i> SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

10:08.206 --> 10:09.707
I got you an early birthday
gift.

10:09.740 --> 10:12.611
You didn't have to get me
anything.

10:13.778 --> 10:15.814
You say that, but you still
took it.

10:18.115 --> 10:20.785
Wow, it's beautiful!

10:20.818 --> 10:22.353
Do you like it?

10:22.386 --> 10:27.291
I mean, jewelry is not really
my thing, but it's very pretty.

10:27.325 --> 10:29.028
Thank you.

10:29.061 --> 10:31.397
Promise me you'll wear it.

10:33.130 --> 10:35.233
Well, put it on!

10:42.908 --> 10:45.244
You really don't get me.

10:45.277 --> 10:47.946
Well, you look awesome.

10:47.979 --> 10:49.849
Keep it on.

10:58.056 --> 11:01.127
Hey, I brought you something.

11:03.128 --> 11:05.197
I just dug these up.

11:09.333 --> 11:11.369
This is pretty.

11:11.403 --> 11:15.408
Thanks. Crystal got it for me,
early birthday gift.

11:16.942 --> 11:18.943
Where did you find these?

11:18.976 --> 11:20.044
I was just going
through some old boxes.

11:20.077 --> 11:23.081
You know how clutter eats
up the important stuff.

11:24.883 --> 11:28.086
I thought you could put a few
of them up on your wall.

11:28.120 --> 11:30.889
Tell me what she was like?

11:30.922 --> 11:36.128
She was beautiful like you, and
she was very kind also like you.

11:38.296 --> 11:39.998
What else?

11:40.030 --> 11:42.767
She had a laugh.

11:42.801 --> 11:46.371
Oh boy, when you would get her
going, oh my god.

11:46.403 --> 11:49.774
I remember one time, she got an
entire room laughing...

11:49.807 --> 11:52.144
and I don't even think they knew
what was funny.

11:55.147 --> 12:02.021
If she were alive, do you think
she would love me?

12:05.023 --> 12:06.457
She would love you.

12:06.490 --> 12:08.961
She does love you...

12:08.994 --> 12:12.364
when she protects you
in her own way.

12:12.397 --> 12:15.100
The day that your mom left us...

12:15.133 --> 12:17.002
well, that was the day
that I got you.

12:17.034 --> 12:19.971
That was the happiest and
saddest day of my life...

12:20.004 --> 12:21.240
all rolled into one.

12:21.273 --> 12:24.243
Do you think my dad's
out there somewhere?

12:26.177 --> 12:28.147
I don't know, honey.

12:28.179 --> 12:32.450
I suppose if he was, I wouldn't
have ended up with you, huh?

12:44.428 --> 12:46.197
( DOOR CLOSES )

12:48.166 --> 12:50.770
( TAPPING ON GLASS )

12:56.073 --> 12:58.076
Ow!

12:56.073 --> 12:58.076
Ow!

12:59.376 --> 13:01.346
Hey, sorry, did I hit you?

13:01.379 --> 13:03.248
What are you doing here?

13:03.280 --> 13:04.982
I'm not stalking you
or anything, I swear.

13:05.015 --> 13:07.051
Then what are you doing
at my house?

13:07.085 --> 13:08.420
Can't we take a walk?

13:08.452 --> 13:09.987
Where?

13:10.020 --> 13:11.923
I guess I didn't think
this through too much.

13:11.956 --> 13:13.125
Uh--

13:13.158 --> 13:15.528
Fine, wait there,
I'm coming down.

13:22.333 --> 13:25.403
<i> ( SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

13:28.505 --> 13:30.274
Do you want to sit down
or something?

13:30.307 --> 13:33.010
Don't do that.

13:30.307 --> 13:33.010
Do what?

13:33.043 --> 13:35.413
Treat me like I'm a special
case.

13:35.447 --> 13:37.548
All right, so we're walking.

13:37.581 --> 13:40.117
( SNICKERS )

13:37.581 --> 13:40.117
What?

13:40.150 --> 13:42.987
Nothing, you're-- you're
really pretty.

13:43.020 --> 13:45.189
( GIGGLES )

13:43.020 --> 13:45.189
What?

13:45.222 --> 13:47.192
Nothing. Thank you.

13:47.225 --> 13:49.260
Are you laughing at me?

13:51.263 --> 13:54.432
No, sorry, I laugh
when I'm nervous.

13:54.466 --> 13:55.900
I make you nervous?

13:55.933 --> 13:58.636
When we're walking alone,
yes, a little bit.

13:58.669 --> 14:01.105
You have nothing to be nervous
about me, Siren.

14:01.139 --> 14:03.542
So why did you move here?

14:03.575 --> 14:05.143
It's kind of embarrassing.

14:05.176 --> 14:07.112
Well, now you pretty much
have to tell me.

14:07.144 --> 14:09.180
My dad says he's chasing down
a cure for me...

14:09.214 --> 14:11.049
but it never gets anywhere.

14:11.081 --> 14:14.186
I mean, if he'd asked me, I
would have told him not to move.

14:14.219 --> 14:16.221
Oh, okay.

14:16.254 --> 14:18.223
Don't-- don't take that
personally.

14:18.255 --> 14:21.360
I just-- I feel like
I'm a burden sometimes.

14:21.393 --> 14:24.062
We're kids, we're supposed
to be a burden.

14:24.095 --> 14:26.999
It's like our right.

14:27.032 --> 14:29.234
My dad's a bit intense, I guess.

14:29.267 --> 14:31.103
I just never know
what's real with him.

14:31.135 --> 14:33.905
I mean, he's convinced there's
a way to really save me...

14:33.938 --> 14:36.908
but I don't know, he drove away
my mom trying to find a cure.

14:36.942 --> 14:38.911
My mom's gone, too.

14:38.943 --> 14:40.144
I'm sorry.

14:40.178 --> 14:45.283
It's okay, just don't treat me
like I'm a special case, either.

14:45.317 --> 14:47.385
So, where are we walking?

14:47.418 --> 14:49.487
Honestly, you're the local.

14:49.520 --> 14:52.323
I don't have any idea
where any of these paths lead.

14:52.356 --> 14:56.627
Well then if we follow this path
back, it should take me home.

14:56.660 --> 14:58.663
Okay, yeah, that one I knew.

14:58.697 --> 15:00.198
( LAUGHS )

15:04.369 --> 15:07.339
<i> ( SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES )</i>

15:07.371 --> 15:08.439
[SIREN]
Goodnight!

15:08.472 --> 15:10.241
Goodnight.

15:19.717 --> 15:23.187
<i> ( MUSIC CHANGES )</i>

15:24.589 --> 15:26.224
Hey, wait up.

15:26.256 --> 15:27.491
Are you wearing my present?

15:27.524 --> 15:29.394
Yeah.

15:27.524 --> 15:29.394
Good.

15:29.427 --> 15:30.663
It wasn't cheap, you know.

15:32.330 --> 15:34.199
Hey, Siren.

15:32.330 --> 15:34.199
Hey, Adam.

15:34.231 --> 15:37.368
That was really fun yesterday.

15:34.231 --> 15:37.368
Yeah, it was nice.

15:37.402 --> 15:40.138
I like your necklace.
It really catches the light.

15:40.171 --> 15:41.605
Thanks.

15:41.639 --> 15:43.341
Anyway, I'll see you around.

15:48.346 --> 15:51.450
Siren, stay away from him.

15:51.482 --> 15:53.050
Why, do you have a crush on him?

15:53.083 --> 15:56.420
No! I mean, yes.

15:56.453 --> 15:58.756
I have a crush on him,
so stay away.

15:58.789 --> 16:01.459
I'm coming over for dinner
tonight, okay?

16:01.493 --> 16:02.661
I'll have to check with my mom.

16:02.693 --> 16:04.697
No, you won't, it's happening.

16:10.534 --> 16:12.770
It's my job to tell her
when the time is right.

16:12.803 --> 16:16.240
Yes, I agree and guess what,
it's time.

16:16.274 --> 16:18.576
Mom?

16:16.274 --> 16:18.576
What?

16:18.610 --> 16:20.745
I'm just saying, this
is Emerald's daughter...

16:20.778 --> 16:24.182
we're talking about
and she deserves to know.

16:24.215 --> 16:26.718
I mean, look at Crystal. She's
known since she could talk.

16:26.750 --> 16:29.387
It's different for you. This is
a world that makes sense to you.

16:29.421 --> 16:30.655
I'm not one of you.

16:30.687 --> 16:35.326
Yes, you are, honey.
Emerald chose you.

16:35.360 --> 16:38.629
That's good enough, tell Siren.

16:38.663 --> 16:40.331
[SIREN]
Tell me what?

16:40.365 --> 16:43.235
Hey, honey.

16:43.268 --> 16:46.772
Your mom invited us over
to have dinner and to talk.

16:46.804 --> 16:48.206
Talk about what?

16:50.240 --> 16:53.611
Why don't you just come
in first and let's eat.

16:54.578 --> 16:57.448
Just try not to freak out, okay?

16:57.481 --> 17:00.651
Saying that's making me
freak out.

17:06.223 --> 17:08.192
Anyone want to tell me
what's going on?

17:08.226 --> 17:10.561
This isn't gonna be easy, so I'm
just gonna go ahead and say it.

17:10.595 --> 17:11.797
Say what?

17:11.829 --> 17:14.365
Quinn has something she'd
like to tell you.

17:16.134 --> 17:20.305
Right... Crystal?

17:20.337 --> 17:25.609
Oh... wow... okay, here it goes.

17:27.112 --> 17:30.782
So, you know how my mom goes off
to work every couple of years...

17:30.815 --> 17:32.616
and I come live with you?

17:32.650 --> 17:35.454
Three years at sea,
three years on land.

17:35.487 --> 17:37.322
For your job right?

17:38.823 --> 17:43.261
Well, she actually
goes <i> into</i> the ocean.

17:43.294 --> 17:44.596
Like on a submarine?

17:44.628 --> 17:46.397
Like <i> in</i> the ocean.

17:47.699 --> 17:49.334
Mom, are you sending me away?

17:49.366 --> 17:51.103
No, baby.

17:51.135 --> 17:53.805
I mean, you do have to go
into the water for a little bit.

17:53.837 --> 17:56.340
Like three years.

17:57.509 --> 18:00.511
What are you talking about?

18:00.545 --> 18:06.750
Um, you see...

18:06.784 --> 18:09.321
half-breed mermaids live
three years in the water...

18:09.354 --> 18:10.455
and three years on land.

18:10.488 --> 18:13.125
And you are a--

18:13.157 --> 18:14.659
Could you help me here?

18:17.729 --> 18:21.432
Uh... honey, you're a mermaid.

18:23.667 --> 18:25.903
So is your birth mother.
So am I.

18:25.936 --> 18:28.773
Quite a few women in this
town actually.

18:30.307 --> 18:32.477
Okay, very funny.

18:32.509 --> 18:35.913
Then how come I've never spent
like any time in the water then?

18:35.946 --> 18:40.184
Because the change doesn't
happen until your 12th birthday.

18:43.288 --> 18:44.422
Sweetie?

18:44.454 --> 18:46.390
Crystal?

18:46.423 --> 18:48.460
Mom?

18:48.492 --> 18:50.729
Joke's over, right?

18:50.761 --> 18:52.630
My 12th birthday is this
weekend.

18:52.663 --> 18:54.199
I'm not prepared for this.

18:55.500 --> 18:58.636
Okay, remember how I had
to go to summer school...

18:58.670 --> 19:01.573
but that school was out of town?

19:01.605 --> 19:04.776
They were training me
to live in the ocean.

19:04.808 --> 19:08.413
My birthday is before yours,
where's my training?

19:08.445 --> 19:10.814
Your mom made me promise
to protect you...

19:10.847 --> 19:14.786
and she wanted me to keep
all of this secret.

19:14.818 --> 19:18.190
This would explain why I can
control water.

19:18.222 --> 19:19.957
I thought I was losing my mind.

19:19.990 --> 19:21.660
You can do what?

19:21.692 --> 19:23.628
Control water.

19:24.662 --> 19:27.900
That's a mermaid thing, right?

19:28.967 --> 19:30.435
Wait, show us.

19:36.807 --> 19:39.877
<i> ( WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

20:01.833 --> 20:04.669
This is what you were trying
to show me yesterday?

20:04.701 --> 20:06.270
She showed this to you?

20:06.304 --> 20:07.806
Well, tried to.

20:07.838 --> 20:10.841
I just thought she was going
a little cuckoo.

20:10.875 --> 20:13.478
This makes you very unique,
Siren.

20:13.510 --> 20:16.380
Well, I feel unique.

20:17.481 --> 20:20.285
Why do you all look so worried?

20:20.317 --> 20:23.654
We'll need to discuss this
with the others.

20:24.689 --> 20:25.923
If you can do this...

20:25.957 --> 20:31.263
it's possible that your blood
may also have healing powers.

20:33.397 --> 20:35.866
Which would make you very
desirable to the Hunters.

20:35.900 --> 20:38.303
The Hunters?

20:38.336 --> 20:40.271
Well, this has been a really
great dinner!

20:40.305 --> 20:42.274
Thanks for coming over!

20:49.780 --> 20:51.383
( DOOR SLAMS )

20:51.415 --> 20:52.583
Should I go after her?

20:53.718 --> 20:56.488
No, honey, just let her
process it.

20:56.520 --> 20:58.722
( BATH RUNNING )

20:58.756 --> 21:00.759
Is she taking a bath?

21:13.003 --> 21:14.738
You'll be okay.

21:14.771 --> 21:16.707
[TIFFANY]
Oh, honey, that's a great idea.

21:16.740 --> 21:19.644
You should take a bath and get
used to being in the water.

21:19.676 --> 21:21.746
Leave me alone, Mom!

21:24.648 --> 21:25.916
Bye.

21:24.648 --> 21:25.916
Bye.

21:54.746 --> 21:57.816
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

22:29.180 --> 22:30.981
<i> ( MUSIC CHANGES )</i>

22:31.015 --> 22:33.618
Siren, are you okay? Open up!

22:33.651 --> 22:35.086
Siren, open up!

22:36.487 --> 22:38.890
Okay now, sweetie,
when she wakes up...

22:38.923 --> 22:41.092
let's just go slow with her,
okay?

22:41.125 --> 22:42.394
Okay.

22:42.426 --> 22:44.661
We don't want to overwhelm her.

22:44.694 --> 22:46.498
She's had enough for one day.

22:46.530 --> 22:47.566
I understand.

22:49.666 --> 22:51.403
My feet!

22:53.971 --> 22:57.108
Hey, hey, you're okay.

22:59.710 --> 23:01.813
Quinn, where's my mom?

23:01.846 --> 23:04.415
You know, she just ran home to
grab a few things...

23:04.449 --> 23:05.850
but she'll be back very soon.

23:05.883 --> 23:08.052
You were out for a bit.

23:08.085 --> 23:10.422
Siren, how are you feeling?

23:12.123 --> 23:14.859
I thought I had a tail.

23:14.892 --> 23:16.928
What's happening to me?

23:16.961 --> 23:19.497
This is normal, honey,
everybody goes through this.

23:19.529 --> 23:21.499
Everybody does not go
through this!

23:21.531 --> 23:23.434
Everybody that's like us.

23:23.468 --> 23:24.969
And how many people is that?

23:25.001 --> 23:29.473
Well, I'd say about 10 or so
in town...

23:29.507 --> 23:31.543
but there are more of us
out there.

23:31.576 --> 23:33.478
Out where?

23:33.510 --> 23:36.213
In the ocean and in other towns.

23:36.247 --> 23:38.583
I want to know the names
of the others in town.

23:38.615 --> 23:40.818
Why has no one
told me this earlier!

23:40.852 --> 23:42.921
What do you even eat
in the ocean?

23:42.953 --> 23:44.221
How do you breathe?

23:44.255 --> 23:47.225
You are going to develop gills!

23:47.258 --> 23:48.692
What?

23:48.726 --> 23:51.830
Okay, Mom, you're not good
at delivering news.

23:51.863 --> 23:55.133
Okay, they're not bad.
They're actually pretty cool.

23:56.933 --> 23:58.470
How can I turn this off?

23:58.502 --> 24:00.771
A woman's body goes through
several changes...

24:00.805 --> 24:01.873
at your age, honey.

24:01.905 --> 24:03.173
This is not puberty!

24:03.207 --> 24:04.676
I know, but--

24:04.709 --> 24:06.076
Is my real mom alive?

24:09.779 --> 24:12.917
Yes. She lives in the ocean.

24:14.885 --> 24:16.788
This is all a bit hard
to explain.

24:16.820 --> 24:20.090
Can you at least try?

24:20.124 --> 24:26.631
Okay, all mermaids have to stay
on land until they are 12...

24:26.663 --> 24:30.167
and then the half-breeds,
they live in the ocean...

24:30.201 --> 24:32.569
for three years and on land
for three years.

24:32.603 --> 24:34.972
They can't control it.

24:35.006 --> 24:37.742
But the purebloods,
they can go in and out...

24:37.775 --> 24:39.878
of the water as they please?

24:39.911 --> 24:43.981
Wait, my mom could come
and get me anytime she wants?

24:44.015 --> 24:48.553
It's not that easy, Siren.
She's trying to protect you.

24:48.586 --> 24:50.521
From what?

24:50.555 --> 24:54.192
Well, your mom's not just
a mermaid.

24:54.224 --> 24:56.693
She's the leader.

24:56.727 --> 25:00.865
My mom's the leader?

25:00.897 --> 25:02.733
And I barely know how to swim?

25:02.767 --> 25:05.202
Tiffany was keeping you safe,
hidden.

25:06.304 --> 25:07.739
To her, that meant not telling
you all this...

25:07.771 --> 25:08.740
until the time was right.

25:08.772 --> 25:11.009
So she's been lying to me
about everything!

25:11.041 --> 25:13.677
Shh, honey, not here.
Someone might hear us.

25:13.711 --> 25:16.748
Yeah, keep the freak out
to a minimum.

25:18.583 --> 25:20.752
Hi, how are you feeling?

25:20.785 --> 25:23.255
I would like to rest, please.

25:24.622 --> 25:27.625
That's something I can prescribe
without the doctor's consent.

25:27.657 --> 25:31.728
Okay, Siren, we'll be just down
the hall, if you need anything.

25:31.761 --> 25:33.565
Send a nurse for us.

25:33.597 --> 25:35.199
I'm fine.

25:35.231 --> 25:36.667
Bye.

25:38.234 --> 25:41.038
Do you need anything before you
go off to slumber land?

25:41.071 --> 25:43.674
I could use some water.

25:43.708 --> 25:45.243
Coming right up.

25:57.188 --> 26:01.759
I was sensing some--
I don't know...

26:01.791 --> 26:04.562
unwillingness to accept
the truth.

26:06.063 --> 26:09.100
Yeah, there was a little bit
of that.

26:09.133 --> 26:11.836
Other than being totally
freaked out...

26:11.868 --> 26:13.704
and hating her mom
for lying to her.

26:13.738 --> 26:15.874
I think she did okay.

26:19.943 --> 26:22.312
Well, she can't stop this.

26:22.346 --> 26:25.282
I'm just hoping she allows us
to help her through it.

26:25.316 --> 26:27.018
[CRYSTAL] Yeah.

26:29.953 --> 26:32.289
One cup of sleepy-time water.

26:32.323 --> 26:35.692
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

26:35.726 --> 26:40.632
Hello? Hello?

26:42.333 --> 26:43.735
Ms. Phillips?

26:43.768 --> 26:46.837
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES )</i>

27:08.459 --> 27:10.228
You about to throw stones at me?

27:10.260 --> 27:13.064
No, sir, at your window...

27:13.096 --> 27:16.834
but I decided against it
before you came out.

27:16.866 --> 27:17.934
And who are you?

27:17.968 --> 27:19.804
I'm Siren, Adam's friend.

27:19.836 --> 27:23.674
( DOOR OPENS )

27:19.836 --> 27:23.674
Siren...

27:23.708 --> 27:25.009
Well, that's a curious name.

27:25.041 --> 27:26.410
It's the only name
I've ever had...

27:26.443 --> 27:29.079
so it's not very curious to me.

27:29.113 --> 27:31.916
Sounds normal, but that might
have been true...

27:31.949 --> 27:33.985
no matter what they called me.

27:34.018 --> 27:36.153
Well, he's inside, come around.

27:36.186 --> 27:37.755
Thank you.

27:43.760 --> 27:48.432
So, you're one of Adam's
friends.

27:48.465 --> 27:51.368
How old are you?

27:48.465 --> 27:51.368
11, almost 12.

27:51.402 --> 27:55.373
Hm, wow, happy almost birthday
to you.

27:55.405 --> 27:57.241
Thank you.

27:57.907 --> 28:01.346
<i> ( OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

28:19.230 --> 28:20.464
Siren?

28:20.498 --> 28:21.799
( BOTTLE CLINKING )

28:23.299 --> 28:25.936
Sorry, you scared me.

28:29.973 --> 28:33.243
I thought maybe since you
dropped by on me, I might--

28:33.277 --> 28:34.144
Drop by also.

28:34.178 --> 28:37.148
Yeah, but I didn't mean
to almost break...

28:37.181 --> 28:38.915
your dad's things, though.

28:38.949 --> 28:42.787
Don't worry about those ships.
He's got tons of junk here.

28:42.819 --> 28:44.422
I like this one.

28:48.125 --> 28:54.132
Ah, the wailing stick,
it's used to kill large fish.

28:54.164 --> 28:56.032
They say the ball
at the other end...

28:56.066 --> 28:57.535
is used to call them to shore.

28:57.567 --> 29:00.771
Its tip can pierce
through tough skin.

29:00.805 --> 29:04.842
Some fish, the kind that you
might read about.

29:04.875 --> 29:08.813
Well, some fish, they are quite
difficult to catch.

29:08.846 --> 29:10.882
I didn't really read a lot
of books about fish.

29:10.914 --> 29:12.750
No?

29:15.519 --> 29:18.923
Your mom doesn't tell you
any stories?

29:18.955 --> 29:20.824
Are you guys hunters?

29:20.857 --> 29:22.159
Depends on what's being hunted.

29:28.499 --> 29:31.434
That's a tranquilizer gun,
it's not for kids.

29:31.468 --> 29:34.305
Anyway, uh, Siren, what did
you need?

29:34.337 --> 29:36.807
Nothing really...
want to go on a walk?

29:36.840 --> 29:38.041
Dad?

29:38.976 --> 29:42.514
Sure, take a walk.

29:44.181 --> 29:47.585
After all, you have two legs,
don't you?

29:51.454 --> 29:53.590
It was nice of you to stop by.

29:53.624 --> 29:55.026
Yeah?

29:55.058 --> 29:57.494
Unexpected, but nice.

29:57.528 --> 30:00.096
Yeah, well, I needed someone
to talk to.

30:00.130 --> 30:01.232
What about?

30:02.932 --> 30:04.568
I'm gonna sound like a crazy
person.

30:04.602 --> 30:07.438
You can trust me, Siren,
I won't freak out.

30:07.471 --> 30:09.840
People say things like,
"I won't freak out."

30:09.874 --> 30:13.243
But then once you realize
I really do sound crazy...

30:13.277 --> 30:15.446
you might feel differently.

30:15.479 --> 30:19.217
I won't, I promise. Go crazy.

30:19.250 --> 30:22.186
I'm a mermaid.

30:24.153 --> 30:25.222
Wait.

30:29.926 --> 30:32.329
Are you being serious right now?

30:32.363 --> 30:35.099
Okay, I'm starting to get
the crazy bit.

30:47.577 --> 30:51.281
You know, you were just on two
feet and not in the water, so--

30:51.315 --> 30:54.151
You're not going into the water,
right?

30:54.183 --> 30:56.253
I'm not a mermaid yet.

30:56.287 --> 30:59.590
Okay, I'm actually having a hard
time telling if you're joking.

30:59.623 --> 31:01.625
I'm not joking.

31:01.659 --> 31:05.229
I'm kind of freaking out,
actually.

31:05.261 --> 31:07.597
Just tell me I'm crazy.

31:07.631 --> 31:09.400
I'd prefer if I were crazy.

31:09.432 --> 31:13.170
At least that I can understand.

31:13.202 --> 31:15.240
So you're a mermaid?

31:16.941 --> 31:19.277
Wait, so you're really
a mermaid?

31:22.479 --> 31:25.082
You know, my dad tells me
these stories.

31:25.115 --> 31:26.549
Do you have gills?

31:26.583 --> 31:29.053
Gross! No, I don't have gills.

31:29.086 --> 31:31.588
Okay, relax. I was just asking.

31:31.622 --> 31:33.324
How else do you breathe
underwater?

31:36.059 --> 31:38.096
Want to go for a swim?

31:40.263 --> 31:43.233
What kind of stories
did your dad tell you?

31:43.267 --> 31:45.102
They're a bit dark.

31:45.134 --> 31:46.636
You really know how
to cheer a girl up.

31:46.670 --> 31:48.406
Hey, I'm trying.

31:48.439 --> 31:51.175
If it makes you feel any better,
my dad's a bit of a nut.

31:54.611 --> 31:56.414
Are you okay?

31:56.446 --> 31:58.949
Just checking for scales.

31:58.982 --> 32:02.153
Anyway, I want to show you
something, come on.

32:12.195 --> 32:15.432
What is this place?
Why are we here?

32:15.465 --> 32:18.368
My dad got this storage
when we moved here.

32:18.402 --> 32:20.971
As if our house didn't already
have enough junk in it.

32:21.005 --> 32:22.640
At least he trusts you
with the combo.

32:22.673 --> 32:25.742
My mom holds as much information
from me as possible.

32:25.776 --> 32:27.278
It's actually set to my
birthday...

32:27.310 --> 32:30.013
so I kind of just figured
it out.

32:30.047 --> 32:33.617
My dad would kill me if he found
out I was taking you here.

32:40.790 --> 32:44.294
Wow, what exactly does your dad
do again?

32:44.327 --> 32:48.298
You're kind of looking at it.
He collects stuff.

32:48.332 --> 32:50.034
Nautical stuff.

32:50.067 --> 32:52.103
You know, ocean items to
folklore-type things.

32:52.135 --> 32:53.037
Really?

32:53.070 --> 32:55.172
A lot of things about mermaids
actually.

32:55.204 --> 32:56.573
Is that the reason you
moved here?

32:56.606 --> 32:59.009
To be close to my kind?

32:59.042 --> 33:00.410
I guess.

33:00.443 --> 33:03.213
It's not like we had a long
conversation about it.

33:06.250 --> 33:08.251
Here, check this out.

33:09.452 --> 33:13.523
Mermaids and other Sea...
Creatures?

33:22.799 --> 33:25.702
That's the Wailing Stick.

33:27.304 --> 33:28.639
It's the one from the drawing.

33:28.672 --> 33:30.040
He's got a replica in here
somewhere.

33:30.074 --> 33:32.076
Can I see it?

33:32.108 --> 33:34.011
If I can find it.

33:48.491 --> 33:51.162
It's lighter than I would've
thought.

33:51.194 --> 33:52.730
My dad said the core
is balsa wood...

33:52.762 --> 33:54.798
and the outside is something
called snake wood.

33:54.832 --> 33:56.133
It's supposed to be rare.

33:56.165 --> 33:58.201
It's beautiful.

33:59.670 --> 34:01.406
So are you.

34:02.839 --> 34:07.677
I'm sorry. You're really pretty.
That's what I meant.

34:07.711 --> 34:09.246
New shirt?

34:09.277 --> 34:10.547
New shirt?

34:10.581 --> 34:13.518
Come on, we should go.

34:15.351 --> 34:17.187
The crystal ball on the end.

34:17.221 --> 34:19.657
According to the story, if
a mermaid sticks that side...

34:19.690 --> 34:22.326
in the water, it'll call the
other mermaids to her side.

34:22.358 --> 34:24.694
It acts sort of like a distress
signal.

34:24.728 --> 34:29.099
One side kills, and one side
calls for help?

34:29.132 --> 34:30.533
That sounds dangerous.

34:30.567 --> 34:34.170
It is. That's what makes
it a good story.

34:34.204 --> 34:35.639
It's just a replica, Siren.

34:35.672 --> 34:37.474
Don't worry about it,
it's not real.

34:37.507 --> 34:38.809
Great.

34:47.650 --> 34:49.252
Mom?

34:57.827 --> 34:59.230
Mom, you scared me!

34:59.262 --> 35:01.531
You had me worried sick.

35:03.467 --> 35:05.568
I've also been worried sick...

35:05.601 --> 35:07.804
but about having to live
in the ocean.

35:07.838 --> 35:11.609
You should have told me earlier,
given me time to prepare.

35:12.909 --> 35:17.114
I know. I know that.

35:18.447 --> 35:21.719
I wish you could be
out there with me.

35:21.751 --> 35:24.221
You know what somebody
told me once about parenting?

35:24.253 --> 35:25.822
They said that it's a series
of moments...

35:25.856 --> 35:27.858
where you have to let go.

35:27.891 --> 35:30.827
I just didn't think I had
to let go all at once.

35:30.860 --> 35:34.297
I thought I could just
sort of loosen my grip.

35:34.331 --> 35:37.468
Will Crystal be out there
with me at some point?

35:37.501 --> 35:40.738
In a few months, you're on
different clocks, so to speak.

35:40.771 --> 35:45.576
I wish I could change my clock
to be in sync with hers.

35:45.608 --> 35:48.478
It doesn't really work
like that.

35:48.512 --> 35:51.849
Here, there's something I should
have given you a long time ago.

35:51.882 --> 35:53.550
What is it?

35:53.583 --> 35:54.884
It's an aerator.

35:54.918 --> 35:57.688
It's gonna help you
transition from land to sea.

35:57.721 --> 36:01.592
You need to keep this on you
until you're in the water, okay?

36:01.625 --> 36:03.793
What do I do with it?

36:03.827 --> 36:06.397
When your gills start to come
in, you're going to need to--

36:06.429 --> 36:08.431
Ew. Yuck!

36:08.465 --> 36:12.469
When they come in, you need
to put this on both sides...

36:12.501 --> 36:14.371
of your neck like this, okay?

36:14.403 --> 36:18.442
To cover them, so that
you can breathe.

36:18.474 --> 36:23.947
The transition to mermaid the
first time, it's slow and--

36:23.981 --> 36:25.716
Ugly?

36:27.583 --> 36:30.253
Yeah, sure, I was looking for a
nicer word, but--

36:30.286 --> 36:32.822
There's no nice word for ugly.

36:35.324 --> 36:36.393
I'm gonna miss you.

36:36.425 --> 36:38.362
I'm going to miss you, too.

36:39.829 --> 36:41.865
Have you heard
of the Wailing Stick?

36:45.668 --> 36:47.704
Where did you hear that?

36:47.737 --> 36:49.940
Boy at my school, he had all
these old books...

36:49.972 --> 36:52.710
and his dad had a replica of it
in his storage locker.

36:52.742 --> 36:53.978
What boy?

36:54.010 --> 36:56.480
Just this new kid, Adam Wiltz.

36:56.512 --> 36:58.248
When did he move here?

36:58.282 --> 36:59.550
I don't know.

36:59.583 --> 37:01.251
How many people did he move
here with?

37:01.284 --> 37:02.885
Why can't we just have
a nice moment?

37:02.918 --> 37:04.420
We had a nice moment.

37:04.454 --> 37:07.358
Now I'm asking you some very
important questions.

37:07.391 --> 37:08.692
I don't know, I met his dad...

37:08.724 --> 37:10.728
but he might have an army living
in his basement.

37:10.760 --> 37:12.963
How did you meet his dad?

37:12.996 --> 37:15.699
Don't talk to him ever again!

37:15.731 --> 37:16.934
Fine.

37:16.967 --> 37:19.537
Is that a real fine
or a pretend fine?

37:22.706 --> 37:24.909
Oh my god, okay.

37:26.309 --> 37:28.478
We're gonna talk about this
more in the morning, okay?

37:28.512 --> 37:29.880
Okay.

37:34.351 --> 37:36.553
No more secrets.

37:36.585 --> 37:38.788
No more secrets.

38:05.414 --> 38:08.885
<i> ( SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

38:41.952 --> 38:44.588
( INDISTINCT WHISPERING )

38:45.655 --> 38:47.624
[TIFFANY] I don't know,
that's all she said...

38:47.657 --> 38:49.492
a new boy and his father.

38:49.525 --> 38:52.929
[CORI]
There's got to me more, right?

38:52.963 --> 38:55.899
They are hunters. You know what
they want her for?

38:55.931 --> 38:57.099
[TIFFANY]
I know, that's why I called you.

38:57.132 --> 38:59.902
I have no useful information,
I thought maybe you would.

38:59.936 --> 39:02.506
Apparently I know less than you.

39:02.539 --> 39:04.141
Maybe we should notify
the others.

39:04.173 --> 39:05.242
I'll take care of it.

39:05.275 --> 39:06.242
I mean, if they're here because
they think someone...

39:06.275 --> 39:08.878
is gonna change, they can't
know who, right?

39:08.911 --> 39:11.681
Who won't know who?

39:11.715 --> 39:13.851
Good morning, did we wake
you up?

39:13.884 --> 39:15.085
Hey there, fishy.

39:15.117 --> 39:17.755
Cori, ssh!

39:17.788 --> 39:18.989
Too soon?

39:22.159 --> 39:23.727
What are you talking about, Mom?

39:23.760 --> 39:25.496
Huh?

39:27.597 --> 39:29.533
No more secrets.

39:31.568 --> 39:33.437
No more secrets.

39:35.070 --> 39:38.708
If these people, these new
people are bad people...

39:38.742 --> 39:41.144
you know, well, bad people do
bad things.

39:41.177 --> 39:44.914
I know what's going on and that
was too vague even for me.

39:51.554 --> 39:53.923
The Wailing Stick.

39:53.956 --> 39:56.025
Only two sets of people
know about it.

39:56.059 --> 39:58.528
One is us, and the other--

39:58.561 --> 40:01.063
The other side of the stick.

40:01.097 --> 40:03.133
Yeah, exactly, the other side
of the stick.

40:03.166 --> 40:08.806
The side that wants to hurt you.

40:08.838 --> 40:10.807
Maybe there's a third kind.

40:10.840 --> 40:14.143
People who just collect stuff
and hear stories.

40:14.177 --> 40:16.747
That's your innocence speaking.

40:16.780 --> 40:18.982
Spend a few years out in the
ocean being hunted by sharks...

40:19.014 --> 40:20.217
and we can talk about it.

40:20.250 --> 40:21.751
Tiffany!

40:20.250 --> 40:21.751
Sorry, it's just, it's early...

40:21.784 --> 40:23.686
and I have a lot going on
in my head right now.

40:23.719 --> 40:25.822
Who are the others?

40:25.856 --> 40:28.192
What do you mean?

40:28.224 --> 40:31.027
You said you'd notify
the others.

40:31.061 --> 40:33.764
The other mermaids.

40:33.797 --> 40:36.567
Spill it. Who are they?

40:36.599 --> 40:38.469
Why don't you come to the
meeting tonight...

40:38.501 --> 40:40.570
and find out for yourself?

40:43.239 --> 40:46.643
<i> ( SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

40:55.184 --> 40:56.953
Gross.

41:25.849 --> 41:29.620
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

41:37.027 --> 41:38.829
Cool.

41:52.309 --> 41:54.211
There you are!
Okay, what's going on?

41:54.244 --> 41:56.914
First you just disappeared right
under my nose yesterday...

41:56.947 --> 41:58.981
and now my mom's called
to your house.

41:59.014 --> 42:00.783
She won't even tell me
what's going on.

42:00.817 --> 42:02.619
She said I'll just get upset.

42:02.652 --> 42:04.221
Siren! Um, can we talk?

42:04.253 --> 42:06.789
Sure.

42:06.822 --> 42:09.326
Not here, somewhere else
private.

42:09.358 --> 42:11.594
Excuse me for a second.

42:11.628 --> 42:14.231
Uh, wait, where are you going!

42:28.711 --> 42:31.248
Listen, Siren, so my dad sat me
down yesterday...

42:31.280 --> 42:33.317
and he told me the stories.

42:33.349 --> 42:37.119
Not so much stories, as history.

42:37.152 --> 42:38.788
I know.

42:38.822 --> 42:40.724
My dad said a pureblood
could save me...

42:40.757 --> 42:42.893
or a half-breed at the time
they change.

42:42.925 --> 42:43.927
And here I am.

42:43.960 --> 42:45.928
Are you guys in on some kind
of elaborate joke?

42:45.961 --> 42:48.264
Me and your dad
partnering up to trick you?

42:48.297 --> 42:49.365
It's more likely than the
alternative.

42:49.398 --> 42:50.500
Barely.

42:50.534 --> 42:53.236
It's your blood, Siren.
I want to help you keep it.

42:53.268 --> 42:55.237
I can't do anything.

42:55.271 --> 42:57.841
My body is changing
and I can't stop it.

42:57.873 --> 43:01.844
Well, what am I supposed to do?
My dad, he's hunting you.

43:01.878 --> 43:04.081
He just doesn't know
it's you yet.

43:04.114 --> 43:05.315
Well, don't tell him.

43:05.347 --> 43:10.119
Right, of course--
but he's my dad!

43:10.152 --> 43:11.320
Adam, he'll kill me.

43:11.353 --> 43:12.554
You don't know that.

43:12.588 --> 43:14.924
Most of the hunters, they're
in it more for the science...

43:14.958 --> 43:16.126
than to hurt anyone.

43:16.159 --> 43:19.162
My dad's just made it personal.
Maybe I can reason with him.

43:19.195 --> 43:21.698
Tell him to choose me over you?

43:21.731 --> 43:25.035
Okay, I won't say anything.

43:26.869 --> 43:31.240
All right... I'll do it.

43:31.273 --> 43:35.846
I'll make you better,
but on my own terms.

43:35.878 --> 43:38.248
Really? Okay, what are your
terms?

43:38.280 --> 43:40.016
Well, no killing me,
that's a term.

43:40.050 --> 43:42.952
Reasonable, what else?

43:42.985 --> 43:45.788
Can we talk about this later?

43:46.356 --> 43:47.758
Yeah.

43:47.791 --> 43:49.660
I just feel light-headed.

43:49.693 --> 43:52.663
Is it because of the,
you know, tail?

43:54.998 --> 43:59.970
I'll be fine. See you around.

44:08.945 --> 44:12.216
Are you and lover boy done
with your secret side meeting?

44:13.248 --> 44:14.717
Siren?

44:16.485 --> 44:17.920
Siren!

44:19.489 --> 44:22.793
Siren! Siren, are you okay?

44:22.826 --> 44:25.829
What did you do to her?

44:22.826 --> 44:25.829
I didn't do anything!

44:27.429 --> 44:29.832
( SUCKING AIR )

44:34.070 --> 44:37.875
( ALARM BLARING )

44:40.376 --> 44:42.913
Where is it?

44:42.945 --> 44:45.449
She didn't bring it.

44:46.882 --> 44:49.351
Principal Strauss, I need help!

44:49.385 --> 44:51.121
What is it, what happened?

44:51.153 --> 44:53.155
Metamorphosis?

44:53.188 --> 44:55.192
She doesn't have her aerator.

44:55.224 --> 44:57.059
All right, let's get her
into my office.

44:57.092 --> 44:58.228
What's an aerator?

44:58.260 --> 45:00.697
This is girls stuff,
just stay here.

45:01.530 --> 45:05.302
All right, one, two, three.

45:12.375 --> 45:13.744
Wow.

45:17.514 --> 45:18.449
Do you need help?

45:18.481 --> 45:20.217
Could you run down to the
medical room...

45:20.250 --> 45:22.853
and get us some ice packs?

45:22.885 --> 45:23.987
Sure.

45:24.019 --> 45:25.755
Lock the door.

45:25.789 --> 45:27.891
Wait, but what about the ice
packs?

45:27.923 --> 45:30.860
Don't need them. Lock the door.

45:34.998 --> 45:36.867
This should help.

45:38.067 --> 45:40.403
( GASPS )

45:38.067 --> 45:40.403
All right.

45:45.809 --> 45:47.811
You're okay now.

45:49.077 --> 45:50.780
You know what's happening to me?

45:50.813 --> 45:52.982
Why do you think I'm always
so hard on you?

45:54.583 --> 45:57.920
We're gonna have a bit
of overlap you and I.

45:57.954 --> 46:00.457
I'm off to the water again
next year.

46:00.489 --> 46:02.424
Are all the teachers mermaids?

46:02.458 --> 46:04.561
Oh, no, some of them
are half-breeds.

46:04.594 --> 46:10.867
This is your gills trying
to turn water into oxygen.

46:10.900 --> 46:13.036
H20?

46:13.068 --> 46:18.108
You know, two hydrogens
to one oxygen?

46:18.141 --> 46:20.811
Hasn't Ms. Harper talked to you
all about this?

46:20.844 --> 46:22.445
Nope.

46:22.478 --> 46:25.516
Oh-- I've stressed this
so much to her.

46:28.318 --> 46:30.586
Hi! I have the ice packs.

46:30.619 --> 46:32.922
Great! I'll be right with you.

46:32.956 --> 46:35.125
All right, put your scarf
thingy on...

46:35.157 --> 46:37.894
and we've got to find you
some place safe.

46:42.398 --> 46:43.432
Ice packs?

46:43.465 --> 46:45.969
Everything is fine,
you can just take 'em back.

46:46.001 --> 46:48.038
Well, if there's really
a fire...

46:48.070 --> 46:50.906
I'd rather just take them
with me outside.

46:50.940 --> 46:52.375
You know, that's fine, too.

46:52.407 --> 46:55.244
Oh, good! Okay.

46:57.447 --> 47:00.851
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

47:25.440 --> 47:27.443
( BELL RINGS )

47:29.512 --> 47:31.882
All right, everyone,
false alarm.

47:31.914 --> 47:33.016
You can go back inside.

47:33.048 --> 47:34.050
All right, come on.

47:34.083 --> 47:37.653
Not you, not you.
Need to get you someplace safe.

47:37.686 --> 47:40.257
Uh, take her to the river room.

47:37.686 --> 47:40.257
Okay.

47:40.289 --> 47:41.891
Ms. Harper...

47:41.925 --> 47:45.528
next week could you please teach
hydrogen composition?

47:45.561 --> 47:46.630
Yes'ums.

47:46.663 --> 47:48.298
Thank you.

47:51.567 --> 47:53.068
What's the river room?

47:53.101 --> 47:54.570
Come on, don't worry.

47:54.603 --> 47:58.207
It doesn't involve water,
if that's what your thinking.

47:58.240 --> 48:01.244
<i> ( SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

48:13.188 --> 48:14.423
[ADAM] Dad?

48:16.458 --> 48:19.128
Dad?

48:29.137 --> 48:32.141
<i> ( MUSIC CHANGES )</i>

48:47.155 --> 48:50.592
Hey! Come back here
with my bike!

48:50.626 --> 48:54.298
I know where you live!
You're my my neighbor!

49:01.336 --> 49:04.407
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES )</i>

49:45.614 --> 49:48.050
Can I see where I'm going now?

49:48.083 --> 49:50.519
Okay, but you have to promise me
not to freak out.

49:50.552 --> 49:53.188
I'm already freaking out.

49:53.222 --> 49:56.326
Okay, but you can't like scream
at me and stuff.

49:56.358 --> 49:58.394
It's not my fault things
are this way.

49:58.427 --> 50:00.630
Okay.

49:58.427 --> 50:00.630
Okay.

50:05.367 --> 50:07.103
Where are we?

50:07.135 --> 50:09.338
We're at a water desalination
plant.

50:11.541 --> 50:13.443
Wait, slow down!

50:13.476 --> 50:16.079
Come on, we're almost there!

50:18.146 --> 50:19.347
This place is so weird.

50:19.382 --> 50:22.452
Well, it's not the weirdest
thing that's happened to you.

50:25.221 --> 50:28.458
( INDISTINCT CHATTER )

50:34.396 --> 50:35.465
Hi!

50:36.565 --> 50:38.333
Look, you have your gills.

50:38.367 --> 50:40.202
Mom, stop, it's embarrassing.

50:40.235 --> 50:41.436
It's not embarrassing.

50:41.471 --> 50:43.373
It's something that's happened
to every single person here.

50:43.405 --> 50:45.340
Except for me.

50:45.373 --> 50:47.409
Are these all the mermaids
in town?

50:47.443 --> 50:49.612
I can't believe that sentence
just came out of my mouth.

50:49.644 --> 50:52.615
Okay, let's move to the front,
there's lots to talk about.

50:56.518 --> 50:58.687
Congratulations, Siren!

50:58.721 --> 51:01.123
We're all routing for you.

51:01.157 --> 51:04.260
So lovely, honey, you've got
nothing to be afraid of.

51:06.661 --> 51:08.297
What's happening?

51:08.331 --> 51:10.834
They're welcoming you,
it's tradition.

51:10.867 --> 51:13.570
Why do I feel so warm?

51:13.603 --> 51:16.840
It's their energy.
Isn't it beautiful?

51:16.873 --> 51:18.508
Yeah?

51:20.742 --> 51:23.212
Welcome to the club, honey.

51:25.882 --> 51:28.552
All right, let's get down
to business.

51:32.188 --> 51:34.724
First order of the day,
who's in charge...

51:34.757 --> 51:36.659
of the bake sale on Thursday?

51:37.827 --> 51:40.163
No, no, no, Betty,
that was a joke, sorry.

51:41.530 --> 51:43.699
No, we have much more serious
business...

51:43.733 --> 51:46.503
to discuss here today, ladies.

51:46.536 --> 51:52.275
Siren Phillips... has become
one of us.

51:52.307 --> 51:55.711
She's currently undergoing
metamorphosis...

51:55.744 --> 51:58.848
which will culminate Saturday
on her 12th birthday.

52:03.351 --> 52:06.388
<i> ( OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

52:21.237 --> 52:22.639
What are you doing in here, kid?

52:22.672 --> 52:24.740
Um-- oh, I'm--

52:24.773 --> 52:26.476
Yeah, that's what I thought,
you're coming with me.

52:26.509 --> 52:29.811
Take your hands off of him!
That's my son.

52:29.844 --> 52:33.849
Sorry. Sir, I didn't know.

52:33.882 --> 52:37.786
Hey, kid, welcome to your
future.

52:46.628 --> 52:50.732
Don't mind him. He's harmless.

52:50.766 --> 52:52.802
What are you doing here?

52:52.835 --> 52:54.771
I was gonna ask you
the same thing.

52:55.938 --> 52:59.642
We found out that there's
at least one in town...

52:59.675 --> 53:02.278
and she's changing.

53:02.311 --> 53:03.813
This is my chance
to save you, son.

53:03.846 --> 53:06.849
Dad, this is crazy,
who are all these guys?

53:06.882 --> 53:08.818
These are the guys that
are gonna save your life...

53:08.851 --> 53:10.353
catching us a fish.

53:10.385 --> 53:12.822
I don't want to be saved,
not like this.

53:12.855 --> 53:14.490
You said yourself, they're
human half the time.

53:14.523 --> 53:16.226
So what?

53:16.259 --> 53:18.293
When a caterpillar turns
into a butterfly...

53:18.327 --> 53:20.663
it's no longer a caterpillar,
right?

53:20.695 --> 53:22.297
I don't know, I guess not.

53:22.331 --> 53:24.300
But people appreciate the
butterfly, Dad.

53:24.333 --> 53:25.434
They don't try and kill it.

53:25.467 --> 53:28.403
You need to get your head
on straight!

53:28.436 --> 53:30.339
They are the hunted,
we are the hunters!

53:30.373 --> 53:33.443
I don't want you blurring
that line anymore.

53:33.476 --> 53:35.244
You understand me?

53:33.476 --> 53:35.244
Yes, sir.

53:35.277 --> 53:38.247
You can do better than that.

53:38.280 --> 53:39.416
Yes, sir!

53:43.753 --> 53:47.657
Come on, I want to show
you around.

53:51.460 --> 53:54.530
(<i> MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

53:58.601 --> 54:00.403
All right, so it's settled
then.

54:00.436 --> 54:02.572
Siren will spend the night
in her own home tonight...

54:02.605 --> 54:04.940
and then be escorted tomorrow
to a safe house...

54:04.974 --> 54:09.379
where she will finish her
transition into the ocean.

54:09.411 --> 54:12.314
Crystal and Ms. Harper
will join you.

54:13.615 --> 54:16.753
There is still so much we
have to show you...

54:16.786 --> 54:18.954
and so very little time.

54:20.056 --> 54:21.624
I just want to say...

54:21.657 --> 54:25.461
and I know it doesn't feel like
it right now...

54:28.396 --> 54:30.799
but you're living
every little girl's dream.

54:30.833 --> 54:34.271
You're officially a mermaid,
honey!

54:37.072 --> 54:39.442
We're so proud of you.

54:41.943 --> 54:45.681
( ALL SINGING )

54:48.650 --> 54:52.621
What's happening, are they
singing?

54:52.655 --> 54:54.624
Wailing.

54:54.657 --> 54:56.293
Each mermaid wail is unique.

54:56.891 --> 54:59.928
You know how whales have
songs and dolphins speak?

54:59.961 --> 55:01.697
It's kind of like that.

55:12.507 --> 55:14.009
[GARY]
What are we looking at here?

55:14.043 --> 55:15.878
[BRODIE]
This is a map of the area.

55:15.911 --> 55:17.713
Couple of our guys spotted
some women...

55:17.746 --> 55:19.348
driving out of town in a hurry.

55:19.382 --> 55:20.583
Could be something.

55:20.615 --> 55:23.753
What's down there?

55:20.615 --> 55:23.753
It's a desalination plant.

55:23.786 --> 55:25.387
[GARY]
That sounds promising.

55:25.420 --> 55:26.922
[BRODIE]
We'll get a team out there.

55:28.090 --> 55:30.526
[ADAM]
So let me get this straight.

55:30.559 --> 55:32.128
A group of mermaids are meeting
at a what plant...

55:32.161 --> 55:33.829
and doing what exactly?

55:33.862 --> 55:34.931
Not now, Adam.

55:34.963 --> 55:36.932
But, Dad, I know who it is.

55:36.965 --> 55:38.967
I mean, I think I know
who's changing.

55:39.001 --> 55:41.903
You do? How?

55:41.936 --> 55:44.507
She told me.

55:44.539 --> 55:46.509
Interesting.

55:46.541 --> 55:50.545
She just gave you her identity.
Who is it?

55:50.579 --> 55:52.382
You have to promise not
to hurt her.

55:52.414 --> 55:55.817
Adam, to heal you,
I need her blood.

55:55.851 --> 55:58.086
She knows. She'll give it
willingly...

55:58.119 --> 55:59.621
if you can promise her safety.

55:59.655 --> 56:01.858
I am not giving anybody a chance
to back out.

56:01.891 --> 56:03.992
Then I'm not saying who it is.

56:04.025 --> 56:07.730
It's the girl who came over
to our house, isn't it?

56:07.762 --> 56:09.798
Who else is just gonna
tell you she's a mermaid?

56:09.831 --> 56:11.000
Dad, no.

56:11.032 --> 56:14.469
I'm sorry, son,
I'm doing this for you.

56:14.503 --> 56:16.840
One day you'll understand.

56:19.909 --> 56:21.911
Send a team over to her house.

56:21.943 --> 56:23.679
Yes, sir!

56:30.786 --> 56:33.889
<i> ( SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

57:14.063 --> 57:16.231
( KNOCK ON DOOR )

57:16.264 --> 57:17.732
Come in.

57:17.766 --> 57:19.568
Hey there, little swimmer.

57:19.601 --> 57:22.070
Please don't call me that.

57:22.103 --> 57:24.906
I have some people I want you
to meet.

57:24.940 --> 57:27.876
This is Amber and Betty...

57:27.909 --> 57:30.112
they're both half-breeds
like you and Crystal.

57:30.144 --> 57:32.081
It's an honor to meet you,
Siren.

57:32.114 --> 57:34.050
Your mother is very important
to us.

57:34.083 --> 57:36.751
And so are you. I'm Betty.

57:36.784 --> 57:37.853
I like your room.

57:37.887 --> 57:39.021
Thanks.

57:39.054 --> 57:42.224
What's that you're holding?

57:42.257 --> 57:44.759
This is a fem stone and it does
lots of things...

57:44.793 --> 57:46.762
much like your necklace there.

57:46.795 --> 57:49.264
This one creates a force field
about six feet around us.

57:49.297 --> 57:52.934
Cool, can I get one
that does that?

57:52.967 --> 57:55.003
Maybe when you come back.

57:55.036 --> 57:59.208
Well, we'll be outside making
sure things stay quiet.

58:01.911 --> 58:04.113
How ya feeling?

58:04.146 --> 58:08.585
I was just thinking, I can't
really bring anything with me.

58:10.018 --> 58:13.154
That's true, but it's all going
to be here when you come back.

58:13.188 --> 58:15.858
If I come back.

58:13.188 --> 58:15.858
Don't speak like that.

58:15.891 --> 58:18.027
You're the one who had me
worrying about sharks.

58:18.059 --> 58:20.028
Your tail is going to keep
most things away.

58:20.061 --> 58:21.897
You're going to swim fast
and hit hard...

58:21.931 --> 58:24.800
and I'm sure you're going to
like the way it feels...

58:24.833 --> 58:26.668
once you get used to it.

58:26.702 --> 58:28.771
And off life support?

58:29.838 --> 58:31.039
Exactly.

58:31.072 --> 58:32.674
We're going to take you down
tomorrow to the safe house...

58:32.708 --> 58:33.675
to complete the change.

58:33.708 --> 58:37.012
Okay, is it going to take
so long each time?

58:37.045 --> 58:38.213
No, it's just the first time.

58:38.246 --> 58:39.447
Once your body gets used
to the change...

58:39.481 --> 58:42.717
it'll just, you know, turn on
and off like a light switch!

58:42.751 --> 58:46.055
Except, I get to choose when
to turn on the lights?

58:47.789 --> 58:49.824
I guess I'm not that good
at analogies.

58:49.858 --> 58:51.626
Similes actually.

58:51.659 --> 58:54.196
Okay, well, look who's paying
attention at school.

58:57.065 --> 58:59.735
It's gonna be beautiful,
you'll see.

59:01.869 --> 59:03.772
Okay?

59:12.181 --> 59:13.816
Love you.

59:14.315 --> 59:18.020
( DOOR OPENS, CLOSES )

59:19.188 --> 59:22.191
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

59:47.081 --> 59:49.085
<i> ( MUSIC STOPS )</i>

01:00:03.297 --> 01:00:06.602
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

01:00:36.297 --> 01:00:38.934
Be quiet, they're here,
we need to move quickly.

01:00:44.440 --> 01:00:46.142
You go towards the front,
I will go towards the back.

01:00:46.175 --> 01:00:48.044
Mom?

01:00:49.744 --> 01:00:51.713
Siren, get in here!

01:00:51.746 --> 01:00:55.116
No! Help!

01:00:51.746 --> 01:00:55.116
Got one!

01:00:55.150 --> 01:00:56.152
[TIFFANY] Get off of me!

01:00:56.184 --> 01:00:57.853
Where's the kid?

01:00:56.184 --> 01:00:57.853
I didn't see!

01:00:57.885 --> 01:00:59.422
She was headed toward you.

01:00:57.885 --> 01:00:59.422
Run, Siren!

01:00:59.454 --> 01:01:00.889
She went towards the back.

01:01:00.922 --> 01:01:02.323
I'm sorry, I couldn't get her
in my condition.

01:01:02.356 --> 01:01:04.994
This is why we don't bring kids
in to do an adult job!

01:01:05.027 --> 01:01:06.961
No! Get off of me!

01:01:06.994 --> 01:01:08.396
What are you doing here?

01:01:08.429 --> 01:01:09.831
I followed. I just wanted
to help.

01:01:09.864 --> 01:01:11.233
You should be at home resting.

01:01:12.266 --> 01:01:14.135
Come on.

01:01:14.168 --> 01:01:16.071
No!

01:01:14.168 --> 01:01:16.071
Hey!

01:01:16.105 --> 01:01:18.307
Run, Siren!

01:01:19.041 --> 01:01:22.178
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES )</i>

01:01:39.228 --> 01:01:41.697
I think we're far enough
away now.

01:01:44.233 --> 01:01:46.335
What are they gonna do
with my mom?

01:01:46.367 --> 01:01:49.471
Are they going to hurt her?

01:01:49.505 --> 01:01:52.141
They'll use her for leverage.
Try to get you to cave.

01:01:52.173 --> 01:01:54.043
I don't think they'll
hurt her.

01:01:54.076 --> 01:01:55.811
Get me to cave?

01:01:55.844 --> 01:02:00.014
This whole thing is a fairytale,
a folklore!

01:02:00.047 --> 01:02:02.250
My blood may not even heal you!

01:02:02.284 --> 01:02:05.153
Look at your neck, Siren,
you have gills growing there.

01:02:05.186 --> 01:02:07.289
Does this seem like a fairytale?

01:02:22.237 --> 01:02:23.905
Once you have changed,
the best they can do...

01:02:23.938 --> 01:02:26.509
is find the location
of the other mermaids.

01:02:26.541 --> 01:02:29.344
Which is pretty useless,
if they're half-breeds.

01:02:29.378 --> 01:02:31.113
They won't hurt her.

01:02:31.146 --> 01:02:32.782
If they do, I'm gonna--

01:02:32.815 --> 01:02:35.351
Listen! I'm gonna do the
best I can to help you guys.

01:02:35.384 --> 01:02:37.820
I'm so thirsty.

01:02:37.853 --> 01:02:39.956
Here.

01:02:47.362 --> 01:02:49.865
Whoa, you weren't kidding.

01:02:51.166 --> 01:02:53.102
I need to go to the river room.

01:02:53.135 --> 01:02:54.303
What's the river room?

01:02:54.335 --> 01:02:57.405
You really don't know much
about what's going on, do you?

01:02:57.438 --> 01:03:00.076
Hey, I'm doing the best
I can to catch up.

01:03:01.309 --> 01:03:04.279
<i> ( OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

01:03:13.155 --> 01:03:15.324
So this is the place my dad
circled on the map...

01:03:15.356 --> 01:03:16.592
back at base camp.

01:03:16.625 --> 01:03:19.360
Do they know about the
safe house?

01:03:19.393 --> 01:03:20.862
What safe house?

01:03:20.896 --> 01:03:22.331
Good, come on.

01:03:23.632 --> 01:03:27.403
Hey, hey, hey--

01:03:30.105 --> 01:03:31.574
It's-- it's me.

01:03:31.606 --> 01:03:34.043
What are you doing out here?

01:03:34.076 --> 01:03:36.846
I'm Gary's son, I wanted to
check this place out...

01:03:36.878 --> 01:03:39.014
but I wasn't sure if you guys
were just a bunch of mermen.

01:03:39.047 --> 01:03:40.182
Yeah, I recognize you.

01:03:40.215 --> 01:03:42.050
Come on, I'll show you
what we found.

01:03:42.083 --> 01:03:44.219
Yeah, I'm coming.

01:04:28.362 --> 01:04:31.567
<i> ( OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

01:04:33.001 --> 01:04:34.903
Is anyone here?

01:04:36.505 --> 01:04:39.441
Hey, it's just me. Relax.

01:04:39.474 --> 01:04:42.211
And teachers here, too.

01:04:42.244 --> 01:04:44.980
Hey, Siren, I'm glad
you're okay.

01:04:45.012 --> 01:04:48.150
They have my mom, Crystal.
They took her.

01:04:48.182 --> 01:04:49.550
I'm sorry, Siren.

01:04:49.583 --> 01:04:53.121
We have to help her,
or at least send someone.

01:04:53.155 --> 01:04:56.425
We will, but you need to rest
and be safe.

01:04:56.458 --> 01:04:58.226
They won't hurt her.

01:04:58.260 --> 01:05:02.498
That's what she would have
wanted, for you to be safe.

01:05:03.965 --> 01:05:05.634
What is this place?

01:05:05.666 --> 01:05:07.201
We call it a safe house...

01:05:07.235 --> 01:05:09.338
because this is where
you come to transition.

01:05:09.371 --> 01:05:11.539
Sort of like a right of passage.

01:05:11.572 --> 01:05:12.641
Once you get in the water...

01:05:12.673 --> 01:05:15.543
it'll take about 30 minutes
for your tail to form.

01:05:15.577 --> 01:05:17.313
It's not as easy
or hocus pocus-y...

01:05:17.346 --> 01:05:19.414
as the fairytales
make it out to be.

01:05:19.447 --> 01:05:20.949
And there's been accidents...

01:05:20.983 --> 01:05:23.085
where people go to the ocean
to change.

01:05:23.117 --> 01:05:25.621
So this gives you a safe
location.

01:05:25.653 --> 01:05:28.724
And once I turn,
they'll let my mom go?

01:05:28.757 --> 01:05:30.626
They'll have no use for her
then.

01:05:32.159 --> 01:05:36.597
Well, then... let's do this.

01:05:36.630 --> 01:05:38.366
Why don't you get cleaned up...

01:05:38.400 --> 01:05:40.269
and then we'll head
over to the pool.

01:05:42.036 --> 01:05:45.173
<i> ( OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

01:05:50.012 --> 01:05:53.382
Oh, hey there, ladies!
Everything okay?

01:05:53.414 --> 01:05:57.518
Well, well, well, look what
the tide dragged in.

01:05:57.552 --> 01:05:58.687
Let me guess.

01:05:58.719 --> 01:06:02.023
You're the leader here on land.
But, you're a half-breed.

01:06:02.056 --> 01:06:05.059
You're not the real leader
out there, are you?

01:06:05.092 --> 01:06:07.996
For a grown man, you sure
spend an awful lot of time...

01:06:08.030 --> 01:06:10.099
studying mermaids, you know?

01:06:10.132 --> 01:06:12.134
It's my life's work actually.

01:06:12.166 --> 01:06:14.635
I know all about your kind.

01:06:14.668 --> 01:06:17.271
So, you here to to negotiate?

01:06:17.304 --> 01:06:22.176
And Adam, I thought you and
Siren had become friends.

01:06:22.210 --> 01:06:23.278
I, I--

01:06:23.311 --> 01:06:24.412
I said are you
here to negotiate?

01:06:24.445 --> 01:06:27.281
I'll speak with the boy,
if it's all the same to you.

01:06:27.315 --> 01:06:31.686
If it's all the same to me, huh?
Well that's very kind of you.

01:06:31.719 --> 01:06:34.789
To be so concerned
with what's okay with me.

01:06:34.822 --> 01:06:37.492
I'll think about that.

01:06:37.525 --> 01:06:39.194
Get inside.

01:06:40.262 --> 01:06:42.498
( WHISTLING )

01:06:48.103 --> 01:06:50.106
Oh, hello...

01:06:51.172 --> 01:06:52.307
ladies of the ocean.

01:06:52.340 --> 01:06:54.476
We're not here to waste any
time, Gary, where is she?

01:06:54.509 --> 01:06:58.246
That's funny, that's exactly
what I was gonna ask you.

01:06:58.280 --> 01:07:00.416
She's inside. She's safe.

01:07:00.449 --> 01:07:04.186
You know we'll never give you
her location, not yet.

01:07:04.219 --> 01:07:05.820
Why don't you just let us
talk to Tiffany...

01:07:05.853 --> 01:07:08.756
and see if Siren will give up
her blood willingly.

01:07:08.789 --> 01:07:09.757
Be reasonable.

01:07:09.791 --> 01:07:11.660
If I was reasonable,
I wouldn't be doing this...

01:07:11.693 --> 01:07:13.429
in the first place, now would I?

01:07:13.461 --> 01:07:16.231
We're willing to make a trade.

01:07:18.166 --> 01:07:19.434
I'm listening.

01:07:19.467 --> 01:07:22.103
Take me instead, let Tiffany go.

01:07:22.137 --> 01:07:25.140
If there is anyone who could
talk the girl into giving up...

01:07:25.172 --> 01:07:27.708
willingly, it's her own mother.

01:07:27.742 --> 01:07:30.479
I don't know, she's pretty.

01:07:30.512 --> 01:07:32.314
I kind of like having her
around.

01:07:32.347 --> 01:07:34.416
Yeah, that will be enough
of that.

01:07:34.449 --> 01:07:36.284
All right, a trade.

01:07:37.885 --> 01:07:39.621
All right, then.

01:07:40.521 --> 01:07:41.790
Brodie.

01:07:53.601 --> 01:07:57.572
Here, walk over to me, darling.
Come on, it's all gonna be fine.

01:07:57.606 --> 01:08:00.542
Just go to Amber.
She'll take care of you.

01:08:00.574 --> 01:08:02.677
How did you find us, anyway?

01:08:02.710 --> 01:08:05.513
It really wasn't that hard.

01:08:05.547 --> 01:08:08.684
We've been monitoring
your chatter in the ocean.

01:08:08.717 --> 01:08:14.423
Your kind likes to talk a lot,
out on the lonely sea.

01:08:16.625 --> 01:08:18.426
You have 4 hours.

01:08:18.460 --> 01:08:24.233
After that, this spear
will not be so clean.

01:08:24.265 --> 01:08:26.600
Come back here with the girl.

01:08:28.502 --> 01:08:29.636
Where is Siren?

01:08:29.671 --> 01:08:32.807
She is safe and you know where.
Go home.

01:08:32.841 --> 01:08:34.408
We'll be in touch soon.

01:08:34.442 --> 01:08:35.810
Wait, we're just gonna
leave her here?

01:08:35.844 --> 01:08:38.881
Go home, Tiffany.
This isn't the place.

01:08:38.912 --> 01:08:40.814
There's too many of them here.

01:08:45.720 --> 01:08:47.356
[GARY] Let her go.

01:08:47.389 --> 01:08:48.724
Not a chance!

01:08:49.490 --> 01:08:51.560
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

01:08:51.591 --> 01:08:53.493
Oh, hey there, Tiffany,
everything okay?

01:08:53.528 --> 01:08:54.895
Not really!

01:09:07.943 --> 01:09:10.645
I-I want to help Siren, please?

01:09:14.783 --> 01:09:16.350
It's-- it's broken.

01:09:16.384 --> 01:09:17.786
What are you doing here?

01:09:17.819 --> 01:09:23.759
<i> ♪ You can look
 but you won't find me ♪</i>

01:09:23.792 --> 01:09:30.631
<i> ♪ I've already gone ♪</i>

01:09:30.663 --> 01:09:36.238
<i> ♪ You can tell
 that I've been well ♪</i>

01:09:36.270 --> 01:09:42.475
<i> ♪ And I keep moving on ♪</i>

01:09:42.510 --> 01:09:45.846
<i> ♪ I'm already gone ♪</i>

01:09:56.791 --> 01:09:58.427
Happy Mermaid Day!

01:10:01.829 --> 01:10:04.733
Thank you, it's really pretty.

01:10:04.765 --> 01:10:06.201
Make a wish.

01:10:08.802 --> 01:10:09.871
What did you wish for?

01:10:09.904 --> 01:10:12.307
I'm not saying.
It ruins the wish.

01:10:12.340 --> 01:10:13.809
I know what I would wish for.

01:10:13.841 --> 01:10:15.510
You'll get it soon enough.

01:10:17.746 --> 01:10:20.815
I also got you this.

01:10:20.849 --> 01:10:23.619
You know what?
I could really use a present.

01:10:25.753 --> 01:10:30.658
Wow. This is beautiful!

01:10:30.692 --> 01:10:34.895
Being a mermaid comes
with a few perks.

01:10:34.929 --> 01:10:36.864
I'm gonna miss you.

01:10:36.898 --> 01:10:37.798
I'm gonna miss you, too.

01:10:40.301 --> 01:10:43.271
But not as much as I'm gonna
miss this bed.

01:10:43.305 --> 01:10:46.942
I know, right?
This place is amazing.

01:10:46.975 --> 01:10:49.878
How do you even sleep
in the ocean?

01:10:49.911 --> 01:10:51.846
Seaweed beds.

01:10:51.880 --> 01:10:54.416
Gross.

01:10:55.917 --> 01:10:58.387
Well, I know you're gonna
do great, Siren.

01:11:05.025 --> 01:11:05.961
I'm excited.

01:11:05.993 --> 01:11:08.663
I haven't been around
a guppy in a while.

01:11:08.697 --> 01:11:11.333
Um, thank you?

01:11:11.365 --> 01:11:14.569
<i> ( SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

01:11:16.938 --> 01:11:20.641
So I just stand here
and a tail forms?

01:11:20.675 --> 01:11:22.444
Yeah, pretty much.

01:11:24.712 --> 01:11:28.516
<i> ( MUSIC CONTINUES )</i>

01:11:33.654 --> 01:11:36.824
Uh, we're gonna have to work
on your form.

01:11:36.858 --> 01:11:38.659
Is it that bad?

01:11:38.693 --> 01:11:42.698
Well, it's not that good.
Let's just put it that way.

01:11:45.600 --> 01:11:47.035
My feet!

01:11:47.068 --> 01:11:48.369
They're fusing together.

01:11:48.403 --> 01:11:50.672
This is freaking me out.

01:11:50.704 --> 01:11:53.841
Okay, just stay calm. I mean,
it doesn't hurt, right?

01:11:53.875 --> 01:11:58.079
No, it just feels weird.

01:11:58.113 --> 01:12:00.349
And you're just normal
right now?

01:12:00.381 --> 01:12:04.018
Three years on land and three
in the water for us half-breeds.

01:12:04.051 --> 01:12:06.721
I didn't make the rules.

01:12:06.755 --> 01:12:08.856
Besides, I haven't even
changed yet. Lucky.

01:12:08.890 --> 01:12:10.959
I don't feel so lucky.

01:12:17.431 --> 01:12:20.668
I have my tail! It's gorgeous!

01:12:20.702 --> 01:12:22.137
That was quick.

01:12:22.170 --> 01:12:24.373
Okay, now you're on-board
with this whole mermaid thing.

01:12:24.405 --> 01:12:26.541
I can't believe it, it's
amazing!

01:12:26.573 --> 01:12:27.942
Let's see how you swim.

01:12:38.987 --> 01:12:41.722
All right. Now let's try my
favorite move.

01:12:41.756 --> 01:12:43.458
A high jump out of the water.

01:12:43.490 --> 01:12:44.792
A high jump?

01:12:44.826 --> 01:12:47.496
Yeah, you dive under, come up
to the surface...

01:12:47.529 --> 01:12:49.631
and give it two big pushes
right before you break...

01:12:49.663 --> 01:12:52.466
and it feels like your flying.

01:12:52.500 --> 01:12:55.570
I'd show you, but I don't have
my tail right now.

01:12:56.871 --> 01:12:58.140
I don't know.

01:12:58.172 --> 01:13:00.574
It's okay, Siren, you can do it!

01:13:00.608 --> 01:13:02.543
All right, I'll do it.

01:13:12.619 --> 01:13:16.557
[SIREN] Mine won't work!
What's your problem?

01:13:17.792 --> 01:13:21.463
Maybe it was <i> three</i> hard pushes
before you break.

01:13:23.131 --> 01:13:25.667
It's okay, it takes some
practice.

01:13:25.699 --> 01:13:27.903
Come on, let's get you
to the water.

01:13:27.935 --> 01:13:30.805
How do I get out of the
water with this tail?

01:13:30.838 --> 01:13:32.807
It's fine, we have a wheelchair
here...

01:13:32.841 --> 01:13:33.809
and we have a truck out back.

01:13:33.841 --> 01:13:35.476
Shot gun!

01:13:33.841 --> 01:13:35.476
Ms. Harper?

01:13:35.510 --> 01:13:37.646
Yeah.

01:13:35.510 --> 01:13:37.646
You have to drive.

01:13:39.847 --> 01:13:41.115
Oh, yeah.

01:13:41.149 --> 01:13:43.819
Okay, Siren, it's time!

01:14:01.703 --> 01:14:04.773
<i> ( OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

01:14:28.195 --> 01:14:29.663
Is anyone here?

01:14:29.697 --> 01:14:32.734
What is this place?

01:14:33.935 --> 01:14:36.671
It's nothing, it's a second
home.

01:14:36.703 --> 01:14:40.174
You don't have a second home.
We looked.

01:14:40.207 --> 01:14:45.546
Nice pool. This is the mermaid
house.

01:14:45.579 --> 01:14:47.882
No, it's not.

01:14:47.916 --> 01:14:51.552
You're a really bad liar.
I like that about you.

01:14:52.886 --> 01:14:55.823
Base, this is Brodie, track me
and send a team.

01:14:55.856 --> 01:14:57.626
We've located the mermaid house.

01:14:57.658 --> 01:15:00.862
( TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING )

01:15:00.895 --> 01:15:04.132
<i> ( DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

01:15:06.568 --> 01:15:07.668
Let's search the house.

01:15:07.703 --> 01:15:09.170
Look for hidden doors, secret
rooms, that kind of thing.

01:15:09.203 --> 01:15:10.739
And somebody start tracking
these girls...

01:15:10.771 --> 01:15:11.939
in case they already left.

01:15:11.972 --> 01:15:15.109
I found something. There's a
truck headed down for the water.

01:15:17.078 --> 01:15:20.015
Stop. She's already changed
and you're too late!

01:15:20.047 --> 01:15:22.917
Yeah, do your homework.
We've got 'til sunset.

01:15:22.951 --> 01:15:24.319
You think you have until
sunset...

01:15:24.351 --> 01:15:26.054
but no one living has ever
caught one of us...

01:15:26.087 --> 01:15:27.589
at the time we changed.

01:15:27.622 --> 01:15:28.923
Yeah, well let's find out,
what do you say?

01:15:28.957 --> 01:15:30.792
Stop!

01:15:31.359 --> 01:15:33.295
( WHISTLING )

01:15:40.734 --> 01:15:42.170
Let 'em through.

01:15:42.203 --> 01:15:44.139
All right, let's load up.

01:15:53.715 --> 01:15:55.283
We've stalled them and the
others are already...

01:15:55.315 --> 01:15:58.086
down by the beach and I'm sure
Siren has changed by now.

01:15:58.118 --> 01:16:00.121
Let's go to the beach.

01:16:01.956 --> 01:16:04.926
(<i> SOFT MUSIC PLAYING )</i>

01:16:11.198 --> 01:16:13.268
Ready for this?

01:16:13.301 --> 01:16:14.836
Not really.

01:16:14.868 --> 01:16:17.805
It's okay, you're gonna
do great.

01:16:17.838 --> 01:16:21.376
I know it's a lot to take in,
but just breathe...

01:16:21.408 --> 01:16:23.177
through your gills.

01:16:23.211 --> 01:16:25.347
And remember what
I taught you in class.

01:16:25.380 --> 01:16:28.283
You didn't cover any of this
in class.

01:16:28.315 --> 01:16:31.318
Oh, yeah.

01:16:31.351 --> 01:16:32.887
Okay.

01:16:33.154 --> 01:16:36.291
<i> ( MUSIC CONTINUES )</i>

01:17:34.481 --> 01:17:37.685
<i> ( MUSIC CHANGES )</i>

01:17:47.228 --> 01:17:48.829
Drop it!

01:17:48.863 --> 01:17:50.865
You tell her
to come back here!

01:17:50.898 --> 01:17:53.134
She can't hear us,
she's in the water.

01:17:53.167 --> 01:17:54.736
You're too late, she's gone.

01:17:54.769 --> 01:17:57.472
She has already fully changed.
You lose!

01:17:57.505 --> 01:17:58.840
My project, it will work!

01:17:58.872 --> 01:18:00.375
She's not your project!

01:18:03.744 --> 01:18:06.247
You look like you'll be changing
pretty soon, won't you?

01:18:06.279 --> 01:18:07.916
Yeah, I suppose you'll do.

01:18:07.948 --> 01:18:08.983
Not a purebreed...

01:18:09.016 --> 01:18:10.984
but you'll just have to give me
